        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6355465-clayton-hansen?shelf=2019">2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2718176927" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1746661231238240462">Harrowing read set in the Philippines jungle as Tamura, a Japanese private, attempts to retreat to northern Leyte as the Americans close in. The desperation of war is beautifully portrayed but it is a grim novel with the final existential reflections blurring the lines on what is kept in our humanness, what is worth keeping after such living. Insanity painted as God&apos;s finger smudging the perception of what constitutes evil in times of utter hopelessness and desperation. Ooka has done a fine job </span>
  <span id="freeText1746661231238240462" style="display:none">Harrowing read set in the Philippines jungle as Tamura, a Japanese private, attempts to retreat to northern Leyte as the Americans close in. The desperation of war is beautifully portrayed but it is a grim novel with the final existential reflections blurring the lines on what is kept in our humanness, what is worth keeping after such living. Insanity painted as God's finger smudging the perception of what constitutes evil in times of utter hopelessness and desperation. Ooka has done a fine job capturing the horror of it all with Tamura as his vehicle. <br /><br />I must also honour the translator who made this accessible in english - no easy task I'd wager.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1746661231238240462" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
